LILONGWE. Lilongwe Magistrate Court has convicted and fined two gay men for outraging public decency after they were caught having sex in a public place in the capital city. Kelvin Gomani performed the gay sex act with Davie Loka in a car park on December 4 this year, the court heard through prosecutor Sergent Ruth Chiunjika.They were answering to offences relating to idle and disorderly persons in public place contrary to Sections 180 to 184 of the Penal Code of the Laws of Malawi.The couple pleaded guilty for engaging in sexual activity.Initially, Gomani and Luka pleaded not guilty to the case but lagter changed plea after the police prosecution team said they were ready with witnesses. Nyasa TV.